To visualize this scenario, we plot the electron density in the minority spin channel of the localized Kohn-Sham orbitals in the ground state (Fig. 4) which represents the ground state and excited state in the photoexcitation process. NV in diamond shows a rather large change in localization and magnitude of the electron densities going from the excited state to the ground state which leads to a considerable change of electric dipole moment. However, V1 center manifests small change in localization and magnitude of the electron densities that suggests small change of electric dipole moment.

